The police in Akwa Ibom State have arrested a dreaded criminal, who allegedly killed over 15 people in the state including a female corps member, Chinwendu Lovina Ezeh.The suspect, Malachi Uwem, 24, is said to be serial killer and leader of a notorious armed robbery gang, which specialises in robbing Point of Sales operators and filling stations. A spokesperson for the police in the state, SP Odiko Macdon, in a statement said the suspect was traced to his hideout at Ikang in Akpabuyo Local Government Area of Cross River State where he and others were arrested after a shootout with police operatives."The said Malachi and (the) gang have killed over 15 persons and have left some of his victims permanently maimed," the PPRO stated.Macdon said some victims were still in the hospital, while others have shut down their businesses because of huge losses.The police spokesperson said the slain NYSC corps member died last week at a hospital in Enugu, Enugu State, after she was shot on February 20 and robbed of her iPhone, credit card, and N7,000 at Ikot Ambang."Only recently, on Monday, 25th April, he shot and killed two young men on the grounds that the village couldn’t meet his demand of N20million, but were only able to raise N5million,” he said."21/2/22, Malachi robbed and killed a lady teacher returning from school in Okobo Ibiono who had stopped over at a POS shop to withdraw money,” the statement read. "5/3/22, Malachi shot and killed Mrs Idongesit Damson in her house in Okobo Ibiono. He also shot one Wisdom, which also led to a protest and blockage of Uyo/Ikot Ekpene Expressway. Several POS shops and filling stations have been robbed by the suspect and his gang in Okobo Ibiono, Itak axis and Uyo."On Thursday, operatives of Special Weapons And Tactics Squad of Akwa Ibom State Command led by CSP Julian Igbudu, traced the hoodlums to their hideouts in Ikang, Akpabuyo Local Government Area Of Cross River State, where Malachi Friday Uwem, his second in command, 31-year-old Wisdom Sunday Akpan, 20-year-old Ndifreke Sunday Ebong and 33-year-old Annansia Umoh resisted arrest and engaged the operatives in a gun duel."In the ensuing milieu, three of the gang members were fatally injured while attempting to escape."The PPRO said police recovered one cut-to-size pump action gun, one locally-made pistol, many cartridges, one gas head with a resemblance of a gun and assorted charms from the suspects.